result.execSummary:
The defendant Dylan R Hildebrandt was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Strangulation and Suffocation, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:10 PM Prosecuting attorney Nathan T. Oswald appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin, Defendant Deunta S Burton appeared by video, Attorney Oren Jakobson for Deunta S Burton appeared in court.  

Derek Phillippi is sworn as a witness.  Testifies to employment with Wood County Sheriff Dept.  Testifies to investigation of an altercation on 01/09/22 that occurred at the jail.  Testifies to contact with alleged victim and description of what occurred.  CMA did not give Burton permission to punch him in the abdomen.  Testifies to conversation with TJN regarding being put in a sleeper hold by Burton.  TJN did not give permission to be put in a sleeper hold.  Testifies to contact with Burton and co-defendant.  Burton was in custody in Wood county Jail on 01/08/22.  Identifies Burton on video screen.  

Atty Jakobson cross examines the witness.  Testifies to when interviews were conducted.  No correctional officers were interviewed.  Camera footage was reviewed and actions are described.  

Atty Oswald asks court to take judicial notice of Wood County Cases 20CF267 and 20CF350.  No objection.  Court takes judicial notice.  

Not guilty plea is entered.  Bond continued.
